---
By: Heraclitus
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 49
    Verse: 3
Tags:
  - Change
---
All is flux, nothing stands still. Nothing endures but change. ... You could
not step twice into the same river, for other waters are ever flowing onto
you. There is nothing permanent except change.
